## 2. License Types

### 2.1 Personal Use License (Free Tier)

You may use the Software without payment provided that:

- You are an individual;
- You are managing less than USD $1,000,000 in aggregate trading capital or
  assets under management ("AUM");
- You are not using the Software for commercial purposes;
- You are not providing services to third parties using the Software.

If you exceed the AUM threshold or engage in commercial use, you must obtain
a Commercial License.

You are solely responsible for determining whether you qualify for the
Personal Use License. Licensor reserves the right to request reasonable
verification of AUM or commercial use status at any time.

Licensor may modify or discontinue the free Personal Use License upon
30 days written notice.

---

### 2.2 Commercial License

A paid Commercial License is required if:

- You use the Software in connection with any business, fund, advisory
  service, or revenue-generating activity;
- You manage or control $1,000,000 USD or more in AUM;
- You provide trading, consulting, or advisory services to third parties
  using the Software;
- You integrate the Software into a commercial product or service;
- You otherwise use the Software for commercial purposes.

Commercial License terms, pricing, and payment structure will be defined
separately by Licensor. Contact: weston@westonplatter.co

